The process of exclusion of the cinemas, which began with the birth of the large multisale complex in periphery, in the long term means death for the insaal cinema in the centre. A process that appears not only inevitable and irrevocable but also carries the trains of cultural crime.
It is mostly affected by historical places full of memories, "it is like a friend to lose with which one has laid a piece of street full of emotions," says the director of the film "Nuovo Cinema Paradiso", who brought him the Oskar and the great price of Cannes. It is the history of a pre-city kino and its nostalgy, which consists of living in a probably forever lost cinema world.
The figures that the Anec, the central commercial association, delivers speak a clear language: in the last five years, the vast amount of 316 traditional cinemas has been closed; these ticks paid most of the cinemas in the large cities: 10 in Florence, 9 in Milan, Naples, Bologna and Rome, 6 in Turin and 5 in Palermo.
Among the most affected regions are the Emilia-Romagna with 82 lost cinemas, followed by Tuscany with 44 and Lombardy with 41.
This proves that the main guilty are the multiplexkinos, because they are just these three regions where the largest number of these modern cinemas has been registered: at 195 in the last 5 years, Lombardy has the lists, 81 are both in Tuscany and in the Emilia Romagna.
"The business has developed in an irrational way," said Paolo Protti, the president of the Anec, "it is useful that new structures are also incurred, but the preservation of the already existing, because a hall in the city closes, not all its clients are ready to visit a multiplexkino in the periphery instead of the old.
And here remains the missing budget for the Fond of the Commercial Association: the debt burden recorded by the State amounts to about 10 million euros.
It is a shame of the ethical and moral view that the government does not respect existing laws.
In order to preserve the sector, between 16 and 18 million euros would be in the year of need."
Interesting is the case of Bologna, the first Italian city, which, due to the fears of the old cinema halls, decided to protect them by an agreement between the municipality and the Anec; it is the first agreement of this kind in Italy that aims to protect and support the traditional cinemas, both in the historical center and in the periphery.
Among the proposed measures are tax advances for the cinema drivers as well as benefits for the public in the area of transport: it will be allowed to go into the transport restricted areas of the centre and also to park at cheaper parking fees.
"It is a delightful initiative," says Giuseppe Tornatore, "I hope that other cities will join our example and also develop new concepts.
Certainly, however, we also need a better audio and video equipment to be able to address the superpower of multiplex halls, because, finally, the audience of today is more demanding.
The defense of the traditional cinema has always been an important theme for me: the closure of the "Supercinema" of Baghiera, the place of my childhood and youth, was the crucial point that led me to set up the "Nuovo cinema paradiso" even though I had played with the thought for ten years.
I have been living in Rome for 25 years; when I pass the Rialto or the Quirinale in Via Nazionale, where I have experienced so many different emotions, I turn to the side in order not to have to see the dust-covered posters.
The links between politics and 'Ndrangheta lead to the arrest of the mayor of Gioia Tauro
"The mayor of Gioia Tauro was willing to adapt the decisions of the municipality to the interests of the Mafia group Piromalli.
The accusations of the lawyer of the Antimafia authorities of Calabria against the mayor Giorgio Dal Torrione and his alternate Rosario Schiavone of the municipality of Gioia Tauro, who were arrested this morning for processing in mafia shops, are serious.
Gioacchino Piromalli, the older intermediary between the clan and the public administration, and its cousin: the lawyer who has the same name as the boss of the clan, had already been sentenced to a sum of 10 million euros at the time for the involvement of criminal associations of the Mafia.
"Every kind of moral and legal norm disregarding," the lawyers wrote, "the two local administrations decided to pay the lawyer Piromalli funds for consultative activities."
"The mafia group had thus been made possible – according to the judges – to enter the councils officially and to participate in the public administration policy."
The President of the Regional Committee of Calabria Agazio Loiero does not agree that it is in its region "all other than an exception to violate connections between local administrations and organised crimes." "There are places where the concentration of the Mafia is greater than in others in which such connections are practically inevitable.
But there are also local politicians who resist the pressure of the 'Ndrangheta: heroes who receive a white West."
The arrests of this morning follow those of last July, with which, according to the police of the Clan Piromalli, they were deprived.
Since the end of April, the municipal council had been dissolved by Gioia Tauro, but already in 1991 – and also at that time due to alleged connections between organized crime and local administration – the local politicians of their municipal offices had been exposed.
Giorgio Dal Torrione, then mayor of the Udc, was elected as head of the middle-right coalition after the election of May 2006.
He shouted scandal when the prefecture ordered the resolution of the municipal council.
He was interested in the Vice-Minister Marco Minniti, whom he claimed to have invented everything for political-strategic reasons. However, the judges in connection with the detention order of this morning explain that the Piromalli clan had even dared to request an amendment to the A3 project.
A hearing action related to the Dal Torrione case has shown the willingness to meet the wishes of an entrepreneur, who is known to be a representative of the large group around the Piromalli – making the actions of the public administration identical to the interests of this clans."
When the energy escapes from the waves, the great ones suddenly run up
It is an unchanging source of money that covers over 70% of the planet's surface and seems to understand only now the world's major energy companies.
Wells, currents and tires are the new renewable energy sources that all now look at, and also seek to occupy, such as giants like Chevron.
The possibility of gaining energy from the movements of the sea has been considered and examined for 70 years; these studies have not accidentally intensified significantly since the first oil crisis.
As the price of oil broke in around 1980, the idea of marine energy is gasped, but now the environmental organizations and the increased oil price are pushing for new impulses in this sector.
The World Energy Council (WEC) in London estimates that 15% of the global energy needs could be covered by the energy generated by the ocean waves.
This would be equal to the double of the energy currently produced by nuclear power plants.
In addition, the currents and tides will come.
Giants in attack.
The first company that now employs marine energy is Enersis, who signed a contract for the construction of a power plant in northern Portugal in 2005.
When this message was published, it seemed to be a revolutionary step.
Two years later, there are now more and more companies from the traditional energy sector, which focus on marine energy production.
"Chevron investigates these technologies" – the speaker of a company known to the US giant in Wall Street Journal – and considers the possibility to cooperate with us."
This concerns the acquisition of an authorisation by the American Energy Commission, which is necessary to launch a project before the coast of Alaska.
This is a not to be underestimated sign, e.g. when one considers that oil is continued by the US in Alaska and President Bush has recently launched the plans for new drilling.
In addition to Chevron, the companies Verdant Power Inc. from New York and Ocean Power from New Jersey are also investing in the new sector; the details are not known, but observers speak of an increasing interest.
Enhanced technologies.
Experts speak of a technology still in the burst, not least because the last doubts of environmental protectionists have not yet been clarified.
To date, projects such as those in Portugal and also Scotland are of a rather small dimension and do not seem to cause any serious environmental problems.
However, technologies with a far greater impact on the environment need to be produced by a large scale of energy.
There are various possibilities: Ocean Power uses a system of connected bows.
The swim of the waves, which the bows move up and down, is transformed into hydraulic pressure through pistons and cylinders within the swimmer.
This drives a turbine, which in turn operates a generator.
The current is then sent via underwater lines to the coast.
To date, there are four planned installations of this type, which are only waiting for state approval. Some of the energy obtained could also be used for military institutions.
Verdant Power, however, already produces energy for a warehouse and a park with the help of undersea turbines in the East River of New York.
The water movements during the tides drive the turbines, which feed the generator by the resulting rotating movement.
According to Verdant, a long snake of possible clients already awaits the necessary authorizations to use these energy sources.
Only the waves, then the tides.
According to the Institute of Electricity Profiting Research, a particular interest deserves the potential that is in tides.
Although it is also an irregular phenomenon, tides are better predictable than wind currents, sun rays and waves, and therefore a more reliable source of power.
Especially the timing energy is what states such as New York, Maine and Alaska and other coastal states have already invested 7.5 million dollars in 2008 – up to 35 million are already planned for 2009.
